The requests send by the client to the server are simulated throurgh Runnable objects. CpuBoundJob and IOBound Job
 are two classes that are Runnable and extends Job class that is also Serializable so that it can be sent over a 
 network. An IOBound object simulates an I/O bound job whereas CPUBound object  simulates a CPU bound job.
 Both of these objects are run by the Thread Pool System. Job object provides set of methods that are used to
 mark time stamps on the request. The parameters of Job object are used to measure the server performance.

